<promed@promedmail.org>

[For a discussion of leptospirosis, see the prior ProMED-mail post
Leptospirosis - Australia: (QL) alert 20110121.0246.

Merritt Clifton, who submitted the 1st news release above, correctly
comments that "my understanding of leptospirosis is that flooding rat
middens to flush out rats would be about the fastest and most
efficient means of spreading the disease that one could imagine.
Leptospirosis typically spreads in flood zones. This would amount to
manufacturing the flood."

Bantul is a town in the Bantul Regency (a political subdivision of a
province) in Yogyakarta Province, in the south-central portion of the
island of Java, Indonesia (for an administrative map of Indonesia, see
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Indonesia_provinces_location_map-en.svg>.
For an interactive map of Indonesia, see
<http://www.travelpost.com/AS/Indonesia/Yogyakarta/Bantul/map/6658721>).

The regency's population is approximately 800 000
(<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bantul_Regency>).

Tangerang, a city in the Province of Banten, Indonesia, is located
about 20 km west of Jakarta
(<http://www.google.com/search?client=safari&rls=en&q=Tangerang&ie=UTF-8&oe=UTF-8>),
which is the capital and largest city of Indonesia, located on the
northwest coast of Java, with a 2010 population of 9 580 000
(<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jakarta>). Jakarta is divided into 5
municipalities: Central, West, South, East, and North Jakarta, each
with subdivisions
(<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jakarta#Administration>). Java has a
lengthy wet season that runs from October until June, which makes it
prone to flooding from swollen rivers in the wet season. Other
contributing factors to flooding in Jakarta include clogged sewage
pipes and waterways that service an increasing population (see
<http://www.thejakartaglobe.com/city/jakarta-will-never-be-free-of-flooding-expert-warns/359533>).
- Mod.ML

I certainly hope that people will be instructed to keep their free
rat poison out of the reach of children and dogs. Dogs will eat rats
that have died from poison and die themselves. - Mod.JW]
